HEADWORD: existing
<hw>existing</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>having existence or
being or actuality; <as>as, much of the beluga caviar <ex>existing</ex>
in the world is found in the Soviet Union and Iran</as>. Opposite of
<ant>nonexistent</ant>.</def> [Narrower terms: <stype>active,
alive</stype>; <stype>extant, surviving</stype>] <see>Also See:
<er>extant</er>.</see>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> existent.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Present. Opposite of <ant>absent</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Presently existing; <as>as, the <ex>existing</ex>
system</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Exit</ent>⟦br⟧
